Node.Notes: Many read "his" instead of "my" with some Hebrew manuscripts and ancient versions. If "my," then something like "An oracle of transgression concerning the wicked is in the midst of my heart."
Uncertain. Tree assumes something like "he flatters himself in his own eyes [too much] to find his own iniquity so as to hate [it]."
Trees assumes a relative clause with relative particle omitted. Also possible simply a negated adjective. Meaning is the same either way.
Most think "mountains of God" functions as a superlative "the highest mountain."
